{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a4f360f4-babe-4429-a6f8-b4346811475f","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Recursive wildcard glob (`**\\*.*`) — **High impact**\n**Line 9 of `EvalHeavy.csproj`:**\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThis forces MSBuild to walk the **entire directory tree** during evaluation to enumerate every file. This is especially costly in repos with deep `node_modules`, large `obj`/`bin` leftovers, or many files. It also defeats MSBuild's glob caching since `*.*` is extremely broad.\n\n### 2. File I/O via property function — **Medium-high impact**\n**Line 13 of `EvalHeavy.csproj`:**\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nCalling `System.IO.File.ReadAllText` during evaluation performs synchronous disk I/O on **every evaluation** (including IDE design-time builds). Property functions that do I/O block the evaluation thread and can't be cached by MSBuild.\n\n### 3. Chained import depth (3 levels) — **Low-medium impact**\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach import adds an XML parse + evaluation pass. Three custom levels on top of the SDK's own imports adds up. In larger repos this pattern tends to grow and compound.\n\n---\n\n### Recommendations\n| Issue | Fix |\n|---|---|\n| `**\\*.*` glob | Narrow the pattern (e.g., `**\\*.txt`) or move to a target so it runs only at build time, not every evaluation |\n| `ReadAllText` in property | Move to a target using `ReadLinesFromFile` task, or embed the value as a property directly |\n| Deep import chain | Flatten into a single `.props` file where possible to reduce parse overhead |\n\nThe recursive glob is by far the biggest offender — it dominates evaluation time in most real-world projects.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6c3f87df-b0b7-4acf-a63f-e97a6bd68d0e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a full picture. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.","outputTokens":544},"id":"d0da7f1c-2625-423c-98f3-7245cfbbdec1","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:09:45.358Z","parentId":"87aa529f-192d-4436-a507-00e012022cb8"}
